30:10.960 --> 30:12.980
that first year? No, no, no, no. It was in 1972. I was 
a senior and, but I, I never could work at bonfire

30:18.960 --> 30:22.980
because we were working those, those hours, 
which. Now wait, I thought you said you began. When

30:26.960 --> 30:27.981
did you enroll? At AM? 69. 69. Oh, okay. Yeah. All 
right. Well, let's jump forward to that. You

30:36.960 --> 30:38.071
mentioned that date. Describe that, that bonfire 
with that date. Oh, well, I was, I guess I was trying

30:42.050 --> 30:46.070
to impress her that I was a student and she was 
impressed, I guess. And we went to the bonfire and

30:46.776 --> 30:51.070
she had never been to anything like that. She was 
from up in Lubbock and never had, she had gone to

30:55.050 --> 30:57.070
West Texas State University. There was nothing 
like that at West Texas State. And this was a big

30:59.050 --> 31:02.070
deal. I mean, and I think for her being in a place 
where there were mainly whites, all whites, and

31:09.490 --> 31:11.510
for, for us to participate in, in the school life 
and participate in what's going on was very, was

31:17.490 --> 31:21.510
very different because that was not what she was 
